		"description": "{html}<div><p>With a ScrollView, when the contentHeight is set to 'auto', the\r\nvery bottom of the scrolling contents ends very abruptly at the\r\nbottom edge of the last view.</p>\r\n<p>My workaround currently is to add an extra (otherwise\r\nsuperfluous) transparent view after the final view.</p>\r\n<p>It would be useful to have a bottom padding property for this\r\nsituation.</p>\r\n<p>Note: this ticket was raised with DonThorp's approval.</p></div>{html}",
